  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "### Description\n\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Bug\n\nCurrently we allow any unicode characters in our names, including different unsafe modifiers (line breaks, RTL overrides, etc).\n\nThat makes it possible to either cause a DoS attack on some users rendering chats unusable or even spoof other users, pretending to be someone else.\n\nYou don't need any special tools and very tiny knowledge to do this attack.\n\nLooks like both desktop and mobile are affected by that.\n\n**NB! it is not enough to filter them on input, we need to filter them on display**",
